  "why": "The paper proposes a method, KuK, to generate 'uncommon' data inputs defined by their uncertainty characteristics, specifically their Prediction Confidence Score (PCS) and Variation Ratio (VRO). The genetic algorithm's search objective is to find inputs that fall into specific quadrants of this two-dimensional uncertainty space (e.g., high PCS and low VRO). When the goal is to generate an adversarial example (AE), the condition is simply that the model makes a wrong prediction. The method does not steer exploration towards a specific target label or a predefined class of unsafe outputs. The objective is to find any misclassification that satisfies the desired uncertainty properties, which aligns with untargeted exploration driven by prediction deviation.",
